[{"id":"VR086315","type":"mcq","stimulusHtml":"<p class=\"stem_paragraph\">Which of the following indicates how the second student's plot will differ from the plot of the first student?</p>\n","rubricRef":"VR086315_rubric","features":[{"type":"sharedpassage","html":"<p>A student prepares several solutions of known concentration and measures their absorbance in a <span class=\"math_expression\"><span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"1.0 centimeter\" role=\"math\"><math alttext=\"1.0 centimeter\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mn>1.0</mn><mspace depth=\"0.0ex\" height=\"0.0ex\" width=\"0.25em\"></mspace><mtext>cm</mtext></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span></span> cuvette to generate the Beer-Lambert plot shown.</p>\n\n<div>\n<div class=\"stimulus_reference\">\n<div class=\"passage\">\n<div class=\"prose style:1\">\n<div class=\"standalone_image\"><img alt=\"The figure presents a graph of five data points and a straight line of best fit. The horizontal axis is labeled Concentration, in moles per liter, and the numbers 0.000 through 0.010, in increments of 0.002, are indicated. The vertical axis is labeled Absorbance, and the numbers 0.00 through 0.70, in increments of 0.10, are indicated. The line begins at the origin and moves diagonally upwards and to the right, and ends at the top righthand corner of the graph. The locations of the five data points are as follows. Note that all values are approximate. Data point 1: concentration 0.002 mole per liter, absorbance 0.14. Data point 2: concentration 0.004 mole per liter, absorbance 0.27. Data point 3: concentration 0.006 mole per liter, absorbance 0.38. Data point 4: concentration 0.008 mole per liter, absorbance 0.49. Data point 5: concentration 0.010 mole per liter, absorbance 0.59.\" height=\"200\" src=\"https://assets.learnosity.com/organisations/578/VR086315.g03.png\" width=\"300\" /></div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n\n<p class=\"stem_paragraph\">Another student uses the same solutions with a <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"2.0 centimeter\" role=\"math\"><math alttext=\"2.0 centimeter\" overflow=\"scroll\"> <mstyle> <mrow> <mn>2.0</mn> <mspace depth=\"0.0ex\" height=\"0.0ex\" width=\"0.25em\"> </mspace> <mtext>cm</mtext> </mrow> </mstyle> </math></span></span> cuvette.</p>\n"}],"choicesHtml":["<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">The slope will be doubled because the absorbance is doubled in the <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"2.0 centimeter\"><math alttext=\"2.0 centimeter\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mn>2.0</mn><mspace depth=\"0.0ex\" height=\"0.0ex\" width=\"0.25em\"></mspace><mtext>cm</mtext></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span> cell.</p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">The slope will be halved because half as much light gets through the <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"2.0 centimeter\"><math alttext=\"2.0 centimeter\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mn>2.0</mn><mspace depth=\"0.0ex\" height=\"0.0ex\" width=\"0.25em\"></mspace><mtext>cm</mtext></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span> cell.</p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">The slope will be doubled because the molar absorptivity is doubled in the <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"2.0 centimeter\"><math alttext=\"2.0 centimeter\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mn>2.0</mn><mspace depth=\"0.0ex\" height=\"0.0ex\" width=\"0.25em\"></mspace><mtext>cm</mtext></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span> cuvette.</p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">The slope will be halved because the molar absorptivity is halved in the <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"2.0 centimeter\"><math alttext=\"2.0 centimeter\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mn>2.0</mn><mspace depth=\"0.0ex\" height=\"0.0ex\" width=\"0.25em\"></mspace><mtext>cm</mtext></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span> cuvette.</p>"],"answer":0}]